proposed_change: change lapse start and end dates to 5/18
notes: **JOHN** These next three lapse reports are all likely related and part of one relapse. This survey was completed 10 seconds before the survey right after it (resp ID R_vHR0jiGhMl5EFQR). This survey reports a lapse on  5-19 16 - 23, the other says 5/20 10-13, and a third ema report on 5/20 reports  overnight lapse on 5-19 23 - 5/20 10 am. Audio reports 5/17 (completed at 11:59 pm) - 5/19 (completed at 1 pm) are all very strange, short, discuss hating their life, and I think suggests likely drinking on all of these days. However the sub completed all emas on 5/17 and 18 and did not report drinking on any of them which goes against this notion. Audio on 5/21 reports they have been drinking the past few days and need to stop. Even though this and the survey below were taken close together, I believe the participant may have been trying to first report a lapse from the previous night (this survey) and then a lapse during the day leading up to the current survey (on the next survey). Data log mentions the sub was "devastated" by her relapse around this time but did not mention dates, however since the audio mentions a multi-day lapse I think we should trust all reports of drinking during this time. Therefore, I propose to change the lapse start and end dates for this lapse to 5/18 to indicate drinking the previous evening (even though the sub reported no drinking at her 23 ema on 5/18, I feel the audio are supportive enough of drinking to overrule that). We could potentially extend this all the way back to 5/17, but that has even more empty lapse reports on 5/18 to go against this decision. I think reporting the previous night lapses at this point makes the most sense.
